<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN344">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>cenne luṇṭa paintōṭṭu maññai</l>
<l>ceṟivaḷai makaḷi rōppaliṟ paṟanteḻuntu</l>
<l>tuṟainaṇi marutat tiṟukku mūroṭu</l>
<l>niṟaicāl viḻupporu ṭaruta loṉṟō</l>
<l>pukaipaṭu kūreri parappip pakaiceytu</l>
<l>paṇpi lāṇmai taruta loṉṟō</l>
<l>viraṇṭiṉu ḷoṉṟā kāmaiyō varitē</l>
<l>kāñcip paṉimuṟi yāraṅ kaṇṇi</l>
<l>kaṇimē vantava ḷalkulav variyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Will it be one, [namely] giving excellent riches to the full amount</l>
<l>along with a village, where the peacock with green [feather] bunches that had eaten</l>
<l>red paddy rises in flight because it is chased by girls</l>
<l>with tight bangles [and then] rests in the myrobalan near the ghat,</l>
<l>or the other, [namely] giving a manliness without merit,</l>
<l>making an enemy by spreading sharpo flames from which smoke rises,</l>
<l>‒ as for it not being one of the two, [that] will be difficult ‒</l>
<l>that line of the hip of her who desires kino tree</l>
<l>as [her] chaplet, [her] garland from dewy shoots of the portia?  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
